Subject Re FM Transmitter ICs Help From Robert Ganter In article writes I am trying to design a small FM transmitter for remote alarm Pretty high frequency for one Is there an FM transmitter IC available that can be used for this purpose Any help circuits info etc will be greatfully Please reply to Yes and I would use the FM transmitter chip from Motorola Linear and Interface Databook a stable cristal oscillator and a mixer SBL from mini circuits lab Everything is done in the FM chip and then mixed up with the oscillator Just have a look at the ARRL There are lots of ideas in there about oscillators and I don't think there are single chip designs for such high frequencies Thanks in Graham Cheers Robert Robert Ganter Universitaet Basel I am a fan Institut fuer Informatik of my plan Basel Switzerland amateurradio packet